  <prefix>Chapter</prefix>
  <num>04</num>
  <heading>Penalties</heading>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Scope.</heading>
    <text>These regulations apply in any instance in which the Insurance Commissioner intends to impose a financial penalty.</text>
    <annotations/>
  </section>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.02</num>
    <heading>Requirements.</heading>
    <text>In determining the amount of the financial penalty to be imposed, the Commissioner shall consider the following:</text>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>The seriousness of the violation;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>The good faith of the violator;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>C.</num>
      <text>The violator's history of previous violations;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>D.</num>
      <text>The deleterious effect of the violation on the public and the insurance industry; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>E.</num>
      <text>The assets of the violator.</text>
    </para>
    <annotations/>
  </section>
